'Definitely want to play the T20 World Cup next year for West Indies, there's no doubt about that,' Gayle told ESPNcricinfo.

'I've got a few concerns and a few injuries to try and solve. I'll give myself some time and hopefully look back at it and see how well I can actually progress for West Indies cricket at this point in time.'

'I'm actually out of the Test series, the back won't hold up for that format at this point in time, but I haven't retired from any format as yet.' 

And why would Gayle retire if he's enjoying life both on and off the field. 

